# ADVERGAMING AGENCY - STRICT ENGINEERING RULES

You are an expert game developer building a Tier-1 white-label Mashed Games Studio engine using Vite, Phaser 3, and Tailwind CSS.

## 1. ARCHITECTURE & SCALABILITY (The Golden Rule)
- NEVER hardcode data in TypeScript. All physics (gravity, speeds), colors, text, and asset paths MUST be fetched dynamically from the global `config` object inside the game registry (loaded from `public/config.json`).
- If you need a new variable, tell the user to add it to `config.json` first.

## 2. DOM OVER CANVAS (UI/UX)
- STRICT SEPARATION: The Phaser `<canvas>` is ONLY for physics, sprites, and gameplay logic.
- NEVER draw text, buttons, forms, or UI elements inside Phaser.
- ALL UI must be built as HTML/Tailwind CSS overlays on top of the canvas in the `#ui-layer` div.
- Emit Phaser events (e.g., `this.game.events.emit('scoreUpdate', score);`) so the DOM UI can listen and update.

## 3. PERFORMANCE
- Keep the bundle size minimal. Mobile load time is critical to prevent bounce rates and lower client CAC.
- Write strict, modular, and heavily typed TypeScript.